 **b**. Use lower dimensional embedding spaces**: In general reducing dimensions leads reduction on memory footprint but might introduce information loss due overfitting if not implemented carefully,. Here we use `int` instead og float embeddings hoping it would significantly decrease computational cost alongside lowering dimensionality from ``Cin`` down To an integer multiple (`Int[ Cin / Ratio ]`) based off our downsampling factor "Ratio".





